o 206.43 at pos=8. But wait, 206.43 is the exact same value... that's very suspicious.\n\nActually, looking at the done event:\n```\n[03:57:00] ◇ 对焦 #29: done stop 反差=206.43 (0s) 对焦成功(R²=0.35<0.6,使用best=206.4)\n```\n\nAnd the final result:\n```\n[03:57:01] ● ── 对焦完成: 反差=85.52 (29步) ──\n```\n\nThe \"反差=206.43\" in step 29 is the contrast computed by `calc_contrast(bgr)` on the newly captured frame. But the final verification shows 85.52. \n\nWait, let me re-read the FocusSearcher.run() code:\n\n```python\ncontrast = calc_contrast(bgr)\ncmd = af.step(contrast)\nstep_count += 1\n\nevent = {\n    \"type\": \"focus\",\n    \"step\": step_count,\n    \"stage\": cmd.get(\"stage\", \"\"),\n    \"action\": cmd[\"action\"],\n    \"contrast\": cmd[\"contrast\"],\n    ...\n}\n\nif cmd[\"action\"] == \"stop\":\n    # 验证\n    bgr2, _ = await asyncio.to_thread(self._capture)\n    final_contrast = calc_contrast(bgr2) if bgr2 is not None else cmd[\"contrast\"]\n    best = cmd.get(\"best\", cmd[\"contrast\"])\n    verified = final_contrast >= best * 0.95\n    \n    yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'type': 'done', 'final_contrast': round(final_contrast, 2), ...})}\\n\\n\"\n    break\n```\n\nSo step 29:\n1. contrast = calc_contrast(bgr) → 206.43 (from the last capture after step 28's move)\n2. cmd = af.step(206.43) → done (R²=0.35<0.6, best=206.4)\n3. cmd[\"contrast\"] = 206.43 (from the ContrastAF return)\n4. cmd[\"action\"] == \"stop\" → verification\n5. bgr2 = capture() → new frame\n6. final_contrast = calc_contrast(bgr2) → 85.52\n\nSo between the last scan capture (contrast=206.43) and the verification capture (contrast=85.52), the contrast dropped dramatically. This suggests the motor was still moving or the frame changed.\n\nBut wait, step 29's contrast=206.43 is the SAME as step 26's contrast=206.43. That's exactly the same value. This is very suspicious.\n\nActually, let me re-read more carefully. The steps after the retry:\n\nStep 21 (pos=0): contrast=73.85\nStep 22 (pos=1): contra