cent points within 10%)\n- The R² check at step 5: best=77.7, but R² might not be ≥0.8\n\nSo the algorithm scanned 20 steps in a flat region before triggering the flat detection. This is too many.\n\n**Issue 2: \"最后聚焦在的位置，不是反差最高位置\"**\n\nThe algorithm stopped at pos=8 (contrast=206.43) via R² fallback, but the verification capture showed contrast=85.52. This means the motor was not actually at the peak position when verification happened.\n\nThe R² fallback returns \"stop\" immediately without moving to the best position. The current position (pos=8) might not be the best position (pos=5 with contrast=206.43).\n\nWait, but pos=8's contrast is also 206.43. So it should be at a peak... but the verification shows 85.52. This suggests the motor moved between the scan capture and the verification capture.\n\nActually, I think I see the issue. When _fit_and_search returns \"stop\", the FocusSearcher immediately does a verification capture. But between the last scan step's capture and the verification capture, there's no additional move. So the motor should be at the same position.\n\nUnless... the motor didn't fully stop. Or the capture function returns a different frame.\n\nHmm, but the contrast went from 206.43 to 85.52. That's a huge drop. This suggests the motor was still moving when the verification capture happened, or the frame changed.\n\nActually, let me re-read the flow:\n\nStep 28 (pos=7): \n1. contrast = calc_contrast(bgr) → 80.03\n2. cmd = af.step(80.03) → \"focus_far, 0.2s\" (continue scanning)\n3. FocusSearcher: move focus_far 0.2s → sleep 0.2s → stop → delay → capture\n4. bgr = new capture\n\nStep 29 (pos=8):\n1. contrast = calc_contrast(bgr) → 206.43 (from the new capture after step 28's move)\n2. cmd = af.step(206.43) → R²=0.35<0.6, fallback to \"stop\", best=206.4\n3. cmd[\"action\"] == \"stop\" → verification\n4. bgr2 = capture() → another capture\n5. final_contrast = calc_contrast(bgr2) → 85.52\n\nSo between step 29's scan capture (206.43) and the verification capture (85.52), the only thing that happened was:\n- The code entered the \"if cmd['action'] == 'stop'\" block\n- Called self._capture() again\n\nThere's no move between them! The motor should be at the same position. So why is the contrast different?\n\nPossibilities:\n1. The motor was still settling after step 28's move\n2. The capture function returns a slightly different frame (timing issue)\n3. There's a real second peak, and the motor is near it, but the frame timing causes variability\n\nActually, I think the issue is that the motor might not have fully stopped. The calc_stable_delay might not be long enough. Let me check:\n\nThe delay is `calc_stable_delay(client) = exposure_time * 2 + 0.5s`. If the exposure time is short (e.g., 1/60s = 0.0167s), the delay would be 0.0167 * 2 + 0.5 = 0.533s. This might not be enough for the motor to fully stabilize.\n\nBut wait, the user's main concern is different. They said:\n1. \"明显在劣化的近方向，还做了好多次无意义尝试\" - Phase 1 wasted 20 steps\n2. \"最后聚焦在的位置，不是反差最高位置\" - final position is not at peak\n3. \"有前后两个焦点，后焦点可以聚焦，反差更高，但是实际算法对上了前面焦点，反差低的\"\n\nFor point 3: the user says there are two focus peaks. The algorithm found the back peak (206.43 at pos=5), but then the R² fallback stopped at pos=8 without moving back to pos=5.\n\nActually wait, the R² fallback returns \"stop\" at the current position (pos=8). But pos=8 has contrast=206.43 (same as pos=5). So it should be at a second peak. But the verification shows 85.52.\n\nI think the key insight is: the R² fallback doesn't move to the best position. It just stops wherever it is. If the current position is not the best, the final contrast will be lower than best.\n\nIn this case:\n- best = 206.4 (at pos=5)\n- current position = pos=8 (contrast was 206.43 during scan, but 85.52 during verification)\n- The R² fallback returns \"stop\" without moving to pos=5\n\nThe fix should be: when R² fallback triggers, still move back to the best position.\n\nBut the user's deeper question is about the two peaks. Let me think about this...\n\nThe scan data (Phase 2, focus_far):\n```\npos 0: 73.85\npos 1: 76.07\npos 2: 79.37\npos 3: 85.06\npos 4: 101.66\npos 5: 206.43  ← peak 1\npos 6: 95.31\npos 7: 80.03\npos 8: 206.43  ← peak 2 (same value!)\n```\n\nThe user says \"后焦点可以聚焦，反差更高\" - the back peak (pos=8) can focus and has higher contrast. But \"实际算法对上了前面焦点，反差低的\" - the algorithm ended up at the front peak with lower contrast.\n\nWait, but pos=5 and pos=8 both have contrast=206.43. How can one be \"higher\" than the other?\n\nUnless the 206.43 at pos=8 is not real. The verification capture shows 85.52, which suggests the motor is NOT at a peak. So the 206.43 at pos=8 might be a false reading (stale frame, motor still moving, etc.).\n\nActually, I think I understand now. The user is saying:\n- There are two physical focus points (front and back)\n- The back focus point has higher contrast\n- The algorithm stopped at the front focus point area, but the contrast there is actually lower\n\nThe 206.43 at pos=8 might be a glitch or the motor hasn't settled. The verification (85.52) is the real contrast at that position.\n\nSo the issues are:\n1. Phase 1 wasted 20 steps in a flat region (should have reversed earlier)\n2. The R² fallback doesn't move to the best position - it just stops\n3. The scan might have found a false peak at pos=8 due to timing/motor issues\n\nLet me now give a clear analysis to the user.\n\nOK, let me re-analyze focusing on the user's specific questions:\n\n**Question 1: \"明显在劣化的近方向，还做了好多次无意义尝试\"**\n\nPhase 1 (focus_near, steps 1-20): contrast starts at 77.71 and never goes higher. It fluctuates between 65-75 for 20 steps. The algorithm should have reversed much earlier.\n\nRoot cause: The _decline_count threshold is 5 consecutive declines, but the data fluctuates (up-down-up-down), so _decline_count never reaches 5. The flat detection only triggers at step 20. The R² check at step 5 doesn't trigger because best (77.7) > 100 is required for R² to cause a retry... wait, let me check:\n\n```python\nif r2 is not None and r2 >= 0.8 and self._best_value <= 100:\n```\n\nbest=77.7 ≤ 100, so if R² ≥ 0.8, it would trigger. But R² might not be ≥ 0.8 with the fluctuating data. The data is relatively flat (all around 70-77), which could have high R² (linear fit to flat data). But the R² calculation uses log(y) and quadratic fit, which might not give high R² for noisy flat data.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The data in Phase 1 is:\n```\n77.71, 70.04, 68.65, 70.20, 66.91, 67.13, 65.36, 71.85, 73.60, 74.69, 72.83, 75.37, 73.53, 71.89, 74.46, 73.47, 72.11, 74.76, 73.41\n```\n\nThis is essentially flat with noise. The best is 77.71 at the start. The algorithm should detect this as a flat region much earlier.\n\nThe _check_flat() function checks if the last 5 points have (max-min)/max < 10%. Let's check at step 10:\n- Steps 6-10: 67.13, 65.36, 71.85, 73.60, 74.69\n- max=74.69, min=65.36, (74.69-65.36)/74.69 = 12.5% > 10% → not flat\n\nAt step 15:\n- Steps 11-15: 72.83, 75.37, 73.53, 71.89, 74.46\n- max=75.37, min=71.89, (75.37-71.89)/75.37 = 4.6% < 10% → flat!\n\nBut _check_flat() is only called when _step_count >= 20. So the flat detection is delayed to step 20.\n\nWait, let me re-read the code:\n```python\n# 平坦区域: 20步无变化 → 反向; 反向也平坦 → 0.5s加速\nif self._step_count >= 20 and self._check_flat():\n```\n\nThe condition is `_step_count >= 20 AND _check_flat()`. So even if the data is flat from step 15, the algorithm doesn't check until step 20. This wastes 5 steps.\n\nThis is a bug! The flat check should happen earlier, like step 10.\n\n**Question 2: \"最后聚焦在的位置，不是反差最高位置\"**\n\nThe R² fallback returns \"stop\" at the current position without moving to the best position. The current position (pos=8) has scan contrast=206.43, but verification contrast=85.52. This means:\n1. The motor is not at the best position (pos=5)\n2. The scan contrast at pos=8 (206.43) might be a false reading\n3. The R² fallback should move to the best position, not just stop\n\n**Question 3: \"有前后两个焦点\"**\n\nThe scan found two peaks:\n- Front peak: pos=5, contrast=206.43\n- Back peak: pos=8, contrast=206.43 (but verification=85.52, so it's false)\n\nThe back peak is likely a false reading. The motor might have been near the front peak, and the 206.43 at pos=8 is from a stale frame or motor timing issue.\n\nBut the user says \"后焦点可以聚焦，反差更高\" - meaning the back focus point is real and has higher contrast. So maybe both peaks are real, but the verification at pos=8 failed because the motor didn't stop properly.\n\nLet me summarize the bugs:\n\n1. **平坦检测延迟**：_step_count >= 20 才检查平坦，应该在 step 10 就检查\n2. **R² fallback 不移动到 best 位置**：直接 stop，当前位置可能不是 best\n3. **扫描中 206.43 出现两次**：可能是电机未稳定或帧缓存问题\n4. **_decline_count 对波动数据不敏感**：上下波动的数据永远不会触发连续5步下降\n\nLet me give a concise analysis.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_bb25ccad8f0f486eb7b76af4","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":30,"offset":215,"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\controlpanel\\autofocus.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"glm-5.2","usage":{"input":134724,"output":6853,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":141577,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783367919856,"responseId":"cht000d6996@dx19f390341592872503"}}
{"type":"message","id":"54208793","parentId":"0693ecb9","timestamp":"2026-07-06T20:00:45.284Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_bb25ccad8f0f486eb7b76af4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"        action = \"focus_near\" if self._direction < 0 else \"focus_far\"\n        dir_name = '近' if self._direction < 0 else '远'\n\n        # 首步\n        if pos == 0:\n            return {\n                \"action\": action, \"duration\": 0.2,\n                \"stage\": \"scan\", \"contrast\": round(contrast, 2),\n                \"message\": f\"开始对焦(方向={dir_name},尝试{self._attempt+1}/3)\"\n            }\n\n        # 峰值确认：best>100 + 下降≥3步 → 样条拟合+黄金分割\n        if self._decline_after_best >= 3 and self._best_value > 100:\n            return self._fit_and_search()\n\n        # 反向：连续5步下降\n        if self._decline_count >= 5:\n            if not self._do_retry():\n                self._state = self.FAILED\n                return {\n                    \"action\": \"stop\", \"duration\": 0,\n                    \"stage\": \"error\", \"contrast\": round(contrast, 2),\n                    \"message\": \"对焦失败(3次重试耗尽)\"\n                }\n            action = \"focus_near\" if self._direction < 0 else \"focus_far\"\n            dir_name = '近' if self._direction < 0 else '远'\n            return {\n                \"action\": action, \"duration\": 0.2,\n                \"stage\": \"scan\", \"contrast\": round(contrast, 2),\n                \"message\": f\"反向(方向={dir_name},尝试{self._attempt+1}/3)\"\n\n[354 more lines in file. Use offset=245 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783368045284}}
