est=41.3,方向=远)\n[04:55:59] ◇ 对焦 #10: scan focus_far 反差=41.33 (0.2s) 采样(best=41.3,方向=远)\n[04:55:57] ◇ 对焦 #9: scan focus_far 反差=39.97 (0.2s) 采样(best=40.0,方向=远)\n[04:55:56] ◇ 对焦 #8: scan focus_far 反差=39.07 (0.2s) 采样(best=39.1,方向=远)\n[04:55:54] ◇ 对焦 #7: scan focus_far 反差=32.97 (0.2s) 开始对焦(方向=远,尝试2/3)\n[04:55:52] ◇ 对焦 #6: scan focus_far 反差=30.33 (0.2s) 反向(方向=远,尝试2/3)\n[04:55:51] ◇ 对焦 #5: scan focus_near 反差=38.7 (0.2s) 采样(best=44.5,方向=近)\n[04:55:49] ◇ 对焦 #4: scan focus_near 反差=41.27 (0.2s) 采样(best=44.5,方向=近)\n[04:55:47] ◇ 对焦 #3: scan focus_near 反差=42.51 (0.2s) 采样(best=44.5,方向=近)\n[04:55:46] ◇ 对焦 #2: scan focus_near 反差=42.8 (0.2s) 采样(best=44.5,方向=近)\n[04:55:44] ◇ 对焦 #1: scan focus_near 反差=44.54 (0.2s) 开始对焦(方向=近,尝试1/3)\n[04:55:44] ○ 对焦开始, X=2384~2888, Y=485~1157, 共338688像素\n[04:55:41] ○ ── 对焦迭代开始 ──\n\n你现在继续给我分析，这是什么问题？\n1. 为什么框选开始对焦之后，就立刻移动，而不是原地先截图分析再开始第一次移动？\n2. 为什么已经明确向恶化方向移动，但没有触发反向？进入平坦区域，但是依然有明显趋势，为什么没有额外判断？\n给我修复计划"}],"timestamp":1783371484533}}
{"type":"message","id":"e5f81a1c","parentId":"5c27bd77","timestamp":"2026-07-06T21:00:10.148Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me carefully analyze the user's test results and answer their questions.\n\n**Test Data Analysis:**\n\nAttempt 1 (focus_near, steps 1-6):\n```\nStep 1: 44.54  (best=44.5) - 初始\nStep 2: 42.80  (best=44.5) - 下降\nStep 3: 42.51  (best=44.5) - 下降\nStep 4: 41.27  (best=44.5) - 下降\nStep 5: 38.70  (best=44.5) - 下降\nStep 6: 30.33  (best=44.5) - 下降 (decline_count=5 → 反向)\n```\n\nSo after 5 consecutive declines, it reversed. That's 6 steps wasted going in the wrong direction.\n\n**Question 1: Why move immediately instead of capturing first?**\n\nLooking at the code flow in FocusSearcher.run():\n```python\n# 2. 初始截图\nbgr, info = await asyncio.to_thread(self._capture)\n# ...\n# 3. 对焦循环\naf = ContrastAF()\nwhile True:\n    contrast = calc_contrast(bgr)  # ← uses the initial capture\n    cmd = af.step(contrast)\n    # ...\n    if cmd[\"action\"] == \"stop\":\n        break\n    # 移动\n    await asyncio.to_thread(self._move_focus, cmd[\"action\"], cmd[\"duration\"])\n```\n\nWait, the initial capture IS used for the first step() call. So step 1 does use the initial capture. But step 1 returns `action=focus_near, duration=0.2` — it moves on the first step.\n\nLooking at `_step_scan`:\n```python\n# 首步\nif pos == 0:\n    return {\n        \"action\": action, \"duration\": 0.2,\n        \"stage\": \"scan\", \"contrast\": round(contrast, 2),\n        \"message\": f\"开始对焦(方向={dir_name},尝试{self._attempt+1}/3)\"\n    }\n```\n\nThe first step always returns a move command. It doesn't analyze whether the direction is correct. It just starts moving in the default direction (focus_near).\n\nThe user's question is: \"为什么框选开始对焦之后，就立刻移动，而不是原地先截图分析再开始第一次移动？\"\n\nThe answer is: the algorithm DOES capture first (step 1 uses the initial capture), but it only has ONE data point. With only one point, it can't know which direction is correct. It has to pick a direction and start moving. The problem is that the default direction (focus_near) was wrong for this scene.\n\nBut actually, the user's concern might be about the initial screenshot. Let me re-read FocusSearcher.run():\n\n```python\n# 2. 初始截图\nbgr, info = await asyncio.to_thread(self._capture)\n# ...\n# 3. 对焦循环\naf = ContrastAF()\nwhile True:\n    contrast = calc_contrast(bgr)\n    cmd = af.step(contrast)\n```\n\nSo the flow is:\n1. Capture initial frame\n2. Calculate contrast\n3. Call step(contrast) → pos=0 → returns move command\n4. Move, wait, stop, delay, capture\n5. Back to step 2\n\nSo step 1 DOES use the initial capture. The issue is that with only 1 data point, the algorithm can't determine the correct direction. It defaults to focus_near.\n\nActually, I think the user might be asking: why not take TWO screenshots without moving (to establish a baseline), and then decide which direction to go? But that doesn't make sense either — you need to move to see how contrast changes.\n\nOr maybe the user is asking: why not analyze the initial frame's contrast, and if it's very low (like 44.54), don't just blindly start moving — maybe try a different strategy?\n\nI think the user's point is: the algorithm should capture first, analyze, and then decide the initial direction, rather than always defaulting to focus_near. But with only 1 data point, you can't determine the direction. You'd need at least 2 points.\n\nActually, re-reading the question: \"为什么框选开始对焦之后，就立刻移动，而不是原地先截图分析再开始第一次移动？\"\n\nI think the user is saying: the algorithm should first capture and analyze (determine if the scene is suitable, what the initial contrast is, etc.) before starting to move. Currently, step 1 immediately returns a move command without any analysis.\n\nThe fix could be: in step 1 (pos=0), if contrast is very low (below threshold), try a probe step in one direction, and if it gets worse, reverse immediately. But that's essentially what the algorithm does — it just takes too many steps to reverse.\n\n**Question 2: Why didn't it reverse when clearly going in the wrong direction?**\n\nLooking at the data more carefully:\n\nAttempt 1 (focus_near): 44.54 → 42.80 → 42.51 → 41.27 → 38.70 → 30.33\n- 5 consecutive declines → reversed at step 6\n\nAttempt 2 (focus_far): 32.97 → 39.07 → 39.97 → 41.33 → 41.14 → 42.39 → 43.58 → 41.86 → 39.31\n- Steps 7-13: rising (best=43.58 at step 13)\n- Steps 14-15: declining (41.86, 39.31) → decline_after_best=2\n- Step 16: R² check → \"峰值过低,反向(尝试3/3)\"\n\nWait, step 16 says \"峰值过低,反向(尝试3/3)\". This is the R² check: `r2 >= 0.8 and best_value <= 50`. Since best=43.6 <= 50, and R² was >= 0.8, it reversed.\n\nAttempt 3 (focus_near): 37.54 → 39.67 → 41.29 → 40.86 → 38.20 → 39.64 → 35.98 → 37.61 → 33.72 → 28.28 → 25.18 → 24.32 → 22.19\n- Step 17: 37.54 (start)\n- Step 18: 39.67 (rising)\n- Step 19: 41.29 (rising, best=41.3)\n- Step 20: 40.86 (decline 1)\n- Step 21: 38.20 (decline 2)\n- Step 22: 39.64 (rising! decline_count reset)\n- Step 23: 35.98 (decline 1)\n- Step 24: 37.61 (rising! decline_count reset)\n- Step 25: 33.72 (decline 1)\n- Step 26: 28.28 (decline 2)\n- Step 27: 25.18 (decline 3)\n- Step 28: 24.32 (decline 4)\n- Step 29: 22.19 (decline 5) → reverse, but attempt=3, so FAILED\n\nThe problem in attempt 3:\n- After peak at step 19 (41.29), the data fluctuates: 40.86, 38.20, 39.64, 35.98, 37.61, 33.72, 28.28, 25.18, 24.32, 22.19\n- `decline_count` keeps resetting because occasionally contrast goes up (39.64 after 38.20, 37.61 after 35.98)\n- But the overall trend is clearly downward!\n- `decline_after_best` keeps increasing (never resets), but it only triggers `_fit_and_search` when >= 3 AND best > 50. Since best=41.3 <= 50, it never triggers!\n- The flat check at step 10: data is 37.54, 39.67, 41.29, 40.86, 38.20 — not flat (max-min)/max = (41.29-37.54)/41.29 = 9.1% < 10% → actually this IS flat! But _step_count is now in attempt 3, which starts from 0. So at step 10 of attempt 3 (step 27 overall), _step_count=10, check flat: last 5 = 39.64, 35.98, 37.61, 33.72, 28.28 → (39.64-28.28)/39.64 = 28.7% → not flat.\n- The R² check at step 10 of attempt 3: best=41.3 <= 50, but R² might not be >= 0.8.\n\nWait, but in attempt 2, the R² check DID trigger at step 10 (overall step 16). Let me check:\n- Attempt 2 has 10 data points (steps 7-16)\n- At step 10 of attempt 2 (overall step 16): R² check triggers, best=43.6 <= 50\n\nIn attempt 3:\n- At step 5 (overall step 22): R² check, best=41.3 <= 50, but R² might not be >= 0.8\n- At step 10 (overall step 27): R² check, best=41.3 <= 50, but R² might not be >= 0.8\n\nThe data in attempt 3 is: 37.54, 39.67, 41.29, 40.86, 38.20, 39.64, 35.98, 37.61, 33.72, 28.28\nThis is not a nice quadratic shape — it's noisy and trending down. R² might be low.\n\nSo the core issues are:\n1. `decline_count >= 5` (consecutive) doesn't work for noisy declining data\n2. `decline_after_best >= 3 AND best > 50` doesn't trigger when best <= 50\n3. The flat check doesn't trigger because the data has large fluctuations\n\nThe fix should be:\n- When best <= 50, use `decline_after_best >= 5` (instead of >= 3) to trigger reversal, not requiring best > 50\n- Or: track the overall trend (e.g., linear regression slope) and reverse if clearly negative\n\nBut the user said \"禁止过度开发\". The simplest fix:\n- Remove the `best > 50` condition from the peak confirmation check, or lower it\n- Or: add a check for `decline_after_best >= 8` (no best improvement for 8 steps) → reverse regardless of best value\n\nActually, looking at the code again:\n```python\n# 峰值确认：best>50 + 下降≥3步 → 样条拟合+黄金分割\nif self._decline_after_best >= 3 and self._best_value > 50:\n    return self._fit_and_search(contrast)\n\n# 反向：连续5步下降\nif self._decline_count >= 5:\n    ...\n```\n\nThe problem is:\n1. `decline_after_best >= 3 AND best > 50` — when best <= 50, this never triggers, so the algorithm keeps scanning\n2. `decline_count >= 5` — consecutive declines, but noisy data resets the counter\n\nThe fix:\n- Add a check: `decline_after_best >= 8` → reverse (regardless of best value)\n- This means: if no new best for 8 steps, the direction is wrong → reverse\n\nThis is a minimal change that addresses the issue.\n\nAlso for question 1: \"为什么框选开始对焦之后，就立刻移动\"\n\nThe issue is that step 1 (pos=0) always returns a move command. The initial screenshot is used to compute contrast, but there's only 1 data point so the algorithm can't determine direction.\n\nActually, looking at FocusSearcher.run() again:\n```python\n# 2. 初始截图\nbgr, info = await asyncio.to_thread(self._capture)\n# ...\n# 3. 对焦循环\naf = ContrastAF()\nwhile True:\n    contrast = calc_contrast(bgr)  # ← uses initial capture for step 1\n    cmd = af.step(contrast)  # ← step 1: pos=0, returns move\n```\n\nSo step 1 DOES use the initial capture. But the user might be confused because step 1 shows \"开始对焦\" and immediately moves. The user wants the algorithm to first capture, analyze, and then decide.\n\nBut with only 1 data point, you can't determine direction. The algorithm must move to get a second data point. This is fundamental.\n\nHowever, the user's real concern might be: the initial contrast is 44.54, which is low. The algorithm should recognize this and be more cautious (e.g., probe both directions before committing).\n\nBut that's over-development. The simpler fix is: just make the reversal faster when going in the wrong direction.\n\nLet me now draft the fix plan:\n\n### Fix Plan\n\n1. **Add `decline_after_best >= 8` → reverse** (regardless of best value)\n   - When no new best for 8 steps, reverse direction\n   - This catches the case where best <= 50 and `decline_count` keeps resetting\n\n2. **Question 1 answer**: The algorithm DOES capture first. Step 1 uses the initial capture to compute contrast (44.54). But with only 1 data point, it can't determine direction — it must move to get a second point. The issue is not \"moving immediately\" but \"not reversing fast enough when going wrong\".\n\n3. **Question 2 answer**: `decline_count >= 5` requires 5 CONSECUTIVE declines. Noisy data (38.20→39.64→35.98→37.61) resets the counter. And `decline_after_best >= 3 AND best > 50` doesn't trigger when best <= 50. The fix is to add a trend-based reversal.\n\nActually, let me re-read question 2 more carefully: \"为什么已经明确向恶化方向移动，但没有触发反向？进入平坦区域，但是依然有明显趋势，为什么没有额外判断？\"\n\nThe user says the data entered a \"flat region\" but with a clear declining trend. The flat check `(max-min)/max < 10%` might not trigger because the fluctuations are larger than 10%.\n\nLooking at attempt 3 data after peak (step 19, contrast=41.29):\n```\n40.86, 38.20, 39.64, 35.98, 37.61, 33.72, 28.28, 25.18, 24.32, 22.19\n```\n\nThe last 5 at step 27: 39.64, 35.98, 37.61, 33.72, 28.28\n- max=39.64, min=28.28\n- (39.64-28.28)/39.64 = 28.7% → not flat (> 10%)\n\nBut the TREND is clearly downward. The user wants a trend-based check.\n\nThe simplest trend check: compare the average of the first half vs the second half of recent points. If the second half is significantly lower, it's a declining trend.\n\nOr even simpler: `decline_after_best >= N` (no improvement for N steps) → reverse. This is already in the code but only triggers `_fit_and_search` when `best > 50`. I should add: `decline_after_best >= 8` → reverse (regardless of best).\n\nOK let me present the analysis and fix plan to the user.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"## 问题分析\n\n### 问题1：为什么立刻移动？\n\n```\nFocusSearcher.run() 流程:\n  ① 初始截图 → bgr\n  ② contrast = calc_contrast(bgr) → 44.54\n  ③ af.step(44.54) → pos=0, 返回 move(focus_near, 0.2s)\n  ④ 移动 → 截图 → step 2...\n\n初始截图确实被用了（step 1 的 contrast=44.54 就是初始截图）。\n但只有1个数据点无法判断方向，必须移动获取第二个点。\n```\n\n**真正的问题不是\"立刻移动\"，而是\"默认方向错了后反转太慢\"**。attempt 1 走了5步才反转。\n\n### 问题2：为什么明显恶化却没有反转？\n\n```\nattempt 3 数据 (best=41.29 at step 19):\n  step 20: 40.86 ↓  decline_after_best=1\n  step 21: 38.20 ↓  decline_after_best=2\n  step 22: 39.64 ↑  decline_count清零! decline_after_best=3\n  step 23: 35.98 ↓  decline_after_best=4\n  step 24: 37.61 ↑  decline_count清零! decline_after_best=5\n  step 25: 33.72 ↓  decline_after_best=6\n  step 26: 28.28 ↓  decline_after_best=7\n  step 27: 25.18 ↓  decline_after_best=8\n  step 28: 24.32 ↓  decline_after_best=9\n  step 29: 22.19 ↓  decline_after_best=10 → 仍没反转!\n```\n\n**3个原因导致不反转：**\n\n| 原因 | 说明 |\n|------|------|\n| `decline_count >= 5` | 要求**连续**5步下降，但数据波动(38→39→35→37)，反复清零 |\n| `decline_after_best >= 3 AND best > 50` | best=41.3 ≤ 50，条件不满足，永远不触发 `_fit_and_search` |\n| `_check_flat()` | 数据波动幅度 28.7% > 10%，不判定为平坦 |\n\n**整体趋势明显下降（41→22），但算法无法识别趋势。**\n\n## 修复计划（2处精确修改）\n\n| # | 位置 | 修改 | 说明 |\n|---|------|------|------|\n| 1 | `_step_scan` 峰值确认 | 增加：`decline_after_best >= 8` → 反向（不要求 best > 50） | 连续8步无新 best → 方向错误，反转 |\n| 2 | `_step_scan` 平坦检测 | 增加趋势检测：最近8步中，后半均值 < 前半均值 × 0.8 → 反向 | 识别\"非平坦但明显下降\"的趋势 |\n\n需要执行吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"glm-5.2","usage":{"input":192069,"output":4083,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":196152,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1783371484539,"responseId":"cht000d6fc2@dx19f393a363529c2503"}}
